stClassLoader` with the appropriate URLs for `keycloakCodeSourceUrl` and `testCodeSourceUrl`. The helper class is conveniently in the test classes directory.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating class loading issues**\\n\\nI've noticed a potential concern with the `isJava6To8` property set to \\\"1.8\\\" while the `DelegatingSerializationFilter` class might have already been loaded by a parent component through its reference. That reference could load the parent library class, but I'm thinking maybe the class literal doesn’t trigger initialization after all. It seems the child class loading is isolated, so it doesn’t really affect it. Good to clarify!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented a focused coverage test for the active dynamic-access class.\n\nAdded:\n\n- `tests/src/org.keycloak/keycloak-client-common-synced/26.0.9/src/test/java/org_keycloak/keycloak_client_common_synced/DelegatingSerializationFilterInnerOnJava6To8Test.java`\n\nWhat it covers:\n\n- Forces the Java 6–8 adapter path by isolating `DelegatingSerializationFilter` in a child-first class loader with `java.specification.version=1.8`.\n- Provides legacy `sun.misc.ObjectInputFilter` / `sun.misc.ObjectInputFilter$Config` stand-ins via the context class loader.\n- Exercises the public builder API so execution reaches:\n  - `OnJava6To8.getObjectInputFilter(...)`\n  - `OnJava6To8.setObjectInputFilter(...)`\n  - `createFilterMethod.invoke(...)`\n  - `setObjectInputFilterMethod.invoke(...)`\n\nI did not run compilation or tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_065f304d6bc533d60169f9e6df1b4081978405ee447d1e0978\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1536, "output": 2013, "cacheRead": 21504, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25053, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777985222070, "responseId": "resp_065f304d6bc533d60169f9e6c6b0608197ace8f389fc609cad"}}
